# Jackknife — Windsurf IDE Rules

## Project: jackknife
Dual-purpose Python toolkit: importable blades library + project scaffold CLI.
Python 3.12 | Poetry | FastAPI (optional) | Streamlit (default frontend)

## Commands — ALWAYS use poetry run
```
poetry run python          # not python3
poetry run pytest          # not pytest directly
poetry run jackknife       # CLI entry point
poetry run ruff check .    # lint
poetry run ruff format .   # format
poetry run mypy jackknife/ # type check
```

## Branch — ALWAYS branch before changes
```
git checkout -b fix/<name>
git checkout -b feature/<name>
git checkout -b chore/<name>
# main branch is protected — never commit directly
```

## Blade Structure (jackknife/blades/<name>/)
- base.py    → Protocol + ABC (interface first, implementation later)
- models.py  → Pydantic models (extra="forbid", async-safe)
- factory.py → create_X(settings) factory
- __init__.py → public exports

## Core (jackknife/core/)
- get_settings()          → pydantic-settings, lru_cache, env wins over TOML
- get_logger(__name__)    → structlog bound logger
- JackknifeError          → base exception; all blade errors inherit from it
- JackknifeBaseModel      → extra="forbid", str_strip_whitespace=True

## Rules
- Files ≤ 200 lines
- Absolute paths only in config (validator enforces)
- All LLM/storage/data/memory interfaces are async
- Conventional commits: feat: fix: docs: refactor: test: ci: chore:
